column1: #     This table describes the Cepheid stars.
#     How to cite and acknowledge Gaia:
#   description: Period corresponding to the fundamental pulsation mode in the G band time series
#   description: Period corresponding to the first overtone pulsation mode in the G band time series
#   description: Epoch of the maximum of the light curve in the G band
#   description: Epoch of the maximum of the light curve in the BP band
#   description: Epoch of the maximum of the light curve in the RP band
#   description: Epoch of the minimum of the radial velocity curve

#   description: Intensity-averaged magnitude in the BP band
#   description: Intensity-averaged magnitude in the RP band
#   description: Peak-to-peak amplitude of the G band light curve
#   description: Peak-to-peak amplitude of the BP band light curve
#   description: Peak-to-peak amplitude of the RP band light curve
#   description: Peak-to-peak amplitude of the radial velocity curve
#   description: Metallicity of the star from the Fourier parameters of the light curve
#   description: "Fourier decomposition parameter \\texttt{r21G}: A2/A1 (for G band)"
#   description: "Uncertainty on the \\texttt{r21G} parameter: A2/A1 (for G band)"
#   description: "Fourier decomposition parameter \\texttt{r31G}: A3/A1 (for G band)"
#   description: "Uncertainty on the \\texttt{r31G} parameter: A3/A1 (for G band)"

#   description: Number of RP epochs used in the fitting algorithm
#   description: Number of radial velocity epochs used in the fitting algorithm
#   description: Zero point (mag) of the final model of the G band light curve
#   description: Zero point (mag) of the final model of the BP band light curve
#   description: Zero point (mag) of the final model of the RP band light curve
#   description: Number of harmonics used to model the first periodicity of the G-band light curve
#   description: Number of harmonics used to model the first periodicity of the BP-band light curve
#   description: Number of harmonics used to model the first periodicity of the RP-band light curve
#   description: Number of harmonics used to model the first periodicity of the radial velocity curve

#   description: Reference time of the Fourier modelled radial velocity curve
#   description: First frequency of the non-linear Fourier modelling

#   description: Second frequency of the non-linear Fourier modelling in the G band
#   description: Error of the second frequency of the non-linear Fourier modelling in the G band

#   description: Errors of the amplitudes of the Fourier model for the first frequency in the G band

#   description: Errors of the phases of the Fourier model for the first frequency in the G band

#   description: Errors of the amplitudes of the Fourier model for the first frequency in the RP band
